thread.title: Dollar Drops to Lowest Level Since Late 2014

author: Ira Iosebashvili
title: Dollar Drops to Lowest Level Since Late 2014
text:
The dollar fell to its lowest level in more than three years Friday as expectations of accelerating growth abroad spurred investors to sell the U.S. currency and pile into the euro.
The ICE Dollar Index, which measures the U.S. currency against a basket of six others, was recently down more than 1% at 90.90, its lowest level since December 2014.
